      "content": "That feeling of being defined solely by a single failure, especially so young, is incredibly heavy and often feels like the end of an entire lifetime. While the future does not guarantee a return to your plans, there is always another potential version of tomorrow where you can begin to heal and find identity beyond this one academic chapter. Many people who feel exactly like you do eventually discover that their worth and future are not determined by one lost path, but by the resilience required to navigate this deep pain until they find their way again.",
